1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 Tomato
1 Cucumber
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Halloumi
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 drizzle olive oil
1 tbs honey
1 drizzle white wine vinegar

• Slice cucumber into thin sticks.
• Thinly slice tomato into wedges.
• Cut halloumi into 1cm-thick slices.
• In a small bowl, combine garlic & herb seasoning, the honey and a splash of water.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook halloumi, until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add garlic-herb mixture and turn to coat.

• Meanwhile, combine mixed salad leaves, tomato and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a medium bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper and set aside.
• Microwave mini flourtortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Build your tacos by topping tortillas with salad, garlic-herb halloumi and cucumber.
• Drizzle over Greek-style yoghurt to serve. Enjoy!